{"body": "I have to agree with @schneems, the interceptor needs to receive the email ready to be sent, which means everything should have already been generated at that point. What if you want to somehow process the email output like you can change headers? You'd now not be able to do that because the order is changed.\r\n\r\nAnyway, As @schneems pointed, a good place for doing that would be a before/around action/filter, seems like the best solution :+1:", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/14349964", "created_at": "2013-03-03T16:50:01Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/9514#issuecomment-14349964", "updated_at": "2013-03-03T16:50:01Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 9514, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/carlosantoniodasilva", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F60b997fd68261ce70cadaf6c8226c042.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/received_events", "gravatar_id": "77237b97a465ae5a293ad323b7296837", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "carlosantoniodasilva", "type": "User", "id": 26328, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/carlosantoniodasilva/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237e8a8bd3543c15100971f"}, "id": 14349964, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/r